{"source_key":"sha256-f88bd5c54ac5fbbfc982c6d403b2565f","record_index":469,"record_hash":"sha256:294fcb2d5347fd172240bed133179f5716e115434c404c96b6f9f62baf097cd3","timestamp":"2026-05-24T14:43:43.808Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: ec9c4c\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1610\nOutput:\n- tool calls that run tests, builds, formatters, or linters\n- later path or commit evidence, if added\n\nWeak signals:\n\n- backfilled turns with only capture-time environment snapshots\n- broad sessions that span unrelated work\n- sidecar review sessions that discuss the branch but did not implement it\n- turns related only through current branch state\n\nThe UI should expose why a turn is highlighted. Reviewers should not have to\nguess why a session appears.\n\n## Privacy And Publication\n\nAgent Trail is more sensitive than local handoff because it is meant to be\nopened by colleagues.\n\nBefore publishing or linking:\n\n- records must be redacted\n- local filesystem paths should not be exposed\n- raw provider session ids should not be exposed\n- hidden/system/developer prompts should not be exposed\n- source records should stay bounded and redacted\n- the user should understand that the trail may contain prompts and tool output\n\nThe first product design needs an explicit publication boundary. Capturing data\ninto GitMeta does not automatically mean every pull request should expose a\npublic or team-visible Agent Trail.\n\n## Permissions\n\nFirst version: public repositories and public metadata only.\n\nThe server may generate or show an Agent Trail only when it can access the PR\nand GitMeta metadata without private credentials. Private repository support\nshould be a later design pass.\n\nFuture policy options:\n\n- GitButler team/workspace members\n- same users who can view the repository\n- same users who can view the pull request\n- explicit share link recipients\n\nFor private repositories, defaulting to repository/PR visibility is probably the\nleast surprising, but do not build that into v1.\n\n## Non-Goals\n\n- no claim that agent sessions authored the pull request\n- no full transcript dump as the main experience\n- no copying transcript records onto pull request targets\n- no product-specific review payloads inside `but-agentlog`\n- no mag\n[TRUNCATED]\nummaries as the source of truth.\n\nThe smallest buildable slice should prove the full path without solving every\nfuture policy:\n\n```text\nGitHub PR URL -> public access check -> metadata fetch -> but-agentlog lookup\n-> review-safe snapshot -> overview page -> session/turn drill-down\n```\n\nIf that path is vague, implementation should wait.\n\n## Remaining Answers Needed\n\nThe big shape is clear enough now: Forge-hosted, public-repo v1, on-demand URL\nentry, generated snapshots, server-side repo cache, GitMeta fetch, and\n`but-agentlog` interpretation.\n\nThere are no major architecture blockers left.\n\nResolved for v1:\n\n- canonical PR target key: PR number as a `but-agentlog` review target,\n  normalized to `gitbutler-review:<number>`\n- metadata ref path: fetch `refs/meta/main` from the public repository resolved\n  from the PR URL\n- lookup inputs: search the PR/review target and the PR head branch\n- ranking: review-target matches rank above branch-only matches\n- snapshot identity: PR number plus metadata ref OID plus selected session/turn\n  keys\n- fork PRs: not supported in the initial version\n- public redaction: no extra public-web redaction layer beyond baseline\n  `but-agentlog` redaction\n\nDeferred until implementation:\n\n- exact projection payload returned from `but-agentlog` to Forge\n- exact dedupe behavior when a session matches both review and branch targets\n- refresh and invalidation behavior for cached snapshots\n- detailed no-data and weak-evidence page copy\n- initial UI wireframe and interaction details\n\n## Implementation Boundary\n\nKeep the primitive crate boring.\n\n`but-agentlog` owns:\n\n- capture\n- redaction\n- GitMeta storage\n- related-session lookup\n- compact skim/read primitives\n- bounded exact record reads\n\nAgent Trail owns:\n\n- PR/review entry point\n- URL and publishing flow\n- permission model\n- review-specific ranking\n- page layout and copy\n- share-specific projection\n- optional generated summaries\n\nIf Agent Trail needs code in this repository, prefer a separate module or crate\nlayered above `but-agentlog`.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T14:43:43.808Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}